article.headline: Rhode Island 76, Duquesne 69
article.story: PITTSBURGH (AP) -- Scott Hazelton had 23 points and eight rebounds as Rhode Island defeated Duquesne 76-69 on Wednesday night. Hazelton led all scorers for the Rams (4-11, 2-2 in Atlantic 10), who were 0-7 away from home and had lost six of their last seven. The Dukes (4-14, 1-4) have lost four in a row. Rhode Island's 76 points were a season high and more than 18 better than their per-game average (57.9) coming in. The Rams never trailed after Hazelton hit a 3-pointer just over five minutes into the game to give Rhode Island a 7-5 lead. The Rams led by 12 at halftime. Parfait Bitee had 12 points and seven assists and Will Daniels 10 points for the Rams, who shot 56 percent from 3-point range. Jack Higgins had a season-high 20 points for Duquesne. Bryant McAllister added 18 points and led the Dukes with six rebounds. Other than McAllister, Duquesne's other four starters combined for nine points.
